@startuml
start

:Citizen contacts agency through website, phone, chat/mobile, or email;
:Create Case with origin, record type, service category, language, and files;
:Verify citizen by phone or email against MDM;

if (Citizen matched?) then (Yes)
  :Link Case to existing Contact;
else (No)
  :Create provisional Contact and mark Case for manual verification;
endif

:Determine case type, priority, division, required skill, and language;
:Route through Omni-Channel by skill, workload, availability, and queue;
:Agent handles Case in Service Console;

if (Case type?) then (Enquiry)
  :Search Knowledge for approved solution;
  if (Solution exists?) then (Yes)
    :Provide approved solution to citizen;
  else (No)
    :Document resolution and create Knowledge draft;
  endif
  :Follow up until citizen confirms resolution;
else (Feedback)
  :Analyze satisfaction level, root cause, and improvement area;
  if (Citizen response required?) then (Yes)
    :Respond and record communication;
  endif
  :Include feedback in reporting and supervisor evaluation;
endif

if (Complex or SLA risk?) then (Yes)
  :Escalate to Supervisor;
endif

:Close Case with resolution summary and audit trail;
:Branch Admin monitors dashboards by division, channel, and agent;

stop
@enduml
